@satyasyasatyasya5746 Insecurity is at the root of narcissism. 

Narcissists portray a confident, self-assured persona as a defense against deep-rooted feelings of inadequacy. The projection takes the place of honest introspection in the mind of the narcissist first & foremost; i.e. the most important person to fool is ones self.

Narcissistic injury is, by definition, a description of the coping mechanisms that engage when the layers of projection are pierced & a narcissist is forced to confront the disparity between persona & self.
